      "side": 1,
      "message": "I talked with Derek about a couple of the questions that I had in the review. Below were his requests on how this should work:\n* When the application is first starting, the GPIO values in the Chassis class should be set to undefined, not 0. When you later add code that takes action based on those Chassis GPIO values, it should not take action if the value is undefined.\n* When the application is first starting, and Gpio::getPreviousValue() is undefined, then the application should just use Gpio::getValue() as the value. It will just do the deglitching/two in a row logic for subsequent cycles when both getValue() and getPreviousValue() are defined. This will have the following results:\n  * The first time a GPIO is successfully read, that value will be used as the value in the Chassis class.\n  * If the first GPIO read fails, but the GPIO has a default value, then that default value will be used as the value in the Chassis class.\n  * Thus, the Chassis class will not need to know if the GPIO has a default value, and the default value will be used.",
      "revId": "8354420d2352c0c1cc0030f12993fef354765c9a",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
