      "side": 1,
      "message": "This name is a little confusing, since it sounds like it would return a GPIO object rather than a GPIO value.\n\nI\u0027m guessing the reason it isn\u0027t called getPresence() is because there is another source of presence via the path?\n\nWhat is the planned API when presence via path is implemented? It can\u0027t be called getPresencePath(), since that already returns the path vs. the presence based on the path.\n\nAlso, who will own the logic of determining what the \"true\" chassis presence is, based on ANDing or ORing those two together? Will the Chassis class own that, so the caller doesn\u0027t need to know the details?\n\nIf the Chassis class will own the logic of finding the \"truth\", one naming option would be something like:\n* getPresenceFromGPIO()\n* getPresenceFromPath()\n* getPresence()\n\nNormally the Chassis class user would call getPresence(), and it would return the \"true\" presence based on the other two. The other two would be called by automated tests, and they could be helpful if the Chassis class user needs more details for some reason.\n\nNot a big deal. Just a question/suggestion.",
