      "message": "You are not specifying initial values for these. It likely defaults to 0, but if that is what you want it would be more clear to specify {0}.\n\nHowever, should these actually be std::optional\u003cint\u003e like in the Gpio class? That way you can tell the difference between \"I don\u0027t know the value\" and \"I read a 0 value\".\n\nThis is related to my comment on setting these values in the .cpp file. If these values rely on Gpio::getPreviousValue(), that is not going to be defined in the first monitor cycle. Also, if an attempt to find a line or request it fails, then it won\u0027t have a value in the first monitor cycle.\n\nIf other code is going to call getFaultLatched(), should that code get a 0 in these cases? Or should it know that the value is currently undefined?",
